request.description:
Returns the profile of the currently authenticated user. Requires a valid `accessToken` (inherited from collection-level Bearer auth).

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "...",
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "is_active": true,
    "created_at": "2026-01-01T00:00:00"
  }
}
```

Convert **multiple images** to WebP in a single request (max 20 files). One Celery job is created per file.

**Response (`202 Accepted`):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "jobs": [
      { "job_id": "<uuid>", "filename": "photo.jpg", "status": "pending" }
    ],
    "total": 1
  },
  "message": "1 jobs queued"
}
```

Convert **multiple images** to AVIF in a single request (max 20 files). One Celery job is created per file.

**Response (`202 Accepted`):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "jobs": [
      { "job_id": "<uuid>", "filename": "photo.png", "status": "pending" }
    ],
    "total": 1
  },
  "message": "1 jobs queued"
}
```

Convert **multiple images** to any supported format in a single request (max 20 files).

Supported output formats: `png`, `jpg`/`jpeg`, `gif`, `bmp`, `tiff`/`tif`, `webp`, `avif`.

**Response (`202 Accepted`):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "jobs": [
      { "job_id": "<uuid>", "filename": "photo.webp", "status": "pending" }
    ],
    "total": 1
  },
  "message": "1 jobs queued"
}
```
